OBS 08 [=Bulk Density 02] SE corner. Surface with sedimentary dried crust; rocks 1-2(-5)cm to 50% cover.7.5YR7/6 (with touches of 7.5YR6/6). 0-10cm loose horizontal bands. Very hard-set below 10cm depth. Overall 0-30cm as for pit. 0-10cm more fragments 0.3-1.5cm (mode 0.4cm), with 50-60% of vol as pulverised loose <2mm particles. Rocks in 0-10cm ferricrete/laterite pebbles ~0.5cm rounded +/- smooth at 1-2% vol (ferricrete ~7.5YR3/4). Too shallow to reach saprolite or mottles.

Surface with sedimentary dried crust; rocks 1-2(-5)cm to 5% cover. 0-10cm loose horizontal bands and a tendency for the soil to fissure to medium cracks creating irregular semi-tabular blocks. Very hard-set below 10cm depth. Overall 0-30cm as for pit. 0-10cm more fragments 1.5-5cm rough laminr to polyhedral and semi-bedded; with 50-60% of vol as pulverised loose <2mm particles. Rocks scarce or lacking. Too shallow to reach saprolite or mottles.

OBS 06 [=Bulk Density 01]NW corner. Surface with small cracking pattern and sedimentary dried crust; scattered rocks 1-5cm to 5% cover. 0-10cm loose horizontal bands and a tendency for the soil to fissure to medium cracks creating irregular semi-tabular blocks. At 15cm scarce lateral roots of 2-3mm from Muehlenbeckia. Very hard-set below 20cm depth. Overall 0-30cm as for pit. 0-10cm more fragments 0.3-1.5cm (mode 0.4cm), with 50-60% of vol as pulverised loose <2mm particles. Rocks in 0-10cm ferricrete/laterite pebbles <0.5cm rounded +/- smooth at 0.1% vol (ferricrete ~7.5YR3/4). Too shallow to reach saprolite or mottles.
